               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1664" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1664" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1664" type="surname" value="BRIGHTLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1664" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN BRIGHTLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Samuel Brightley, a bricklayer, and live in Crossfield-lane, Deptford. He is the housekeeper—on the afternoon of the 8th of April (Easter Monday,) about three o'clock, I left my house leaving no one in it—I bolted the back door, locked the front, and shut the window and shutters—I came home at half-past seven, and found people round the house—the back door was broken open, and the staple out—I did not lose any thing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1665" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1665" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1665" type="surname" value="BRIGHTLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1665" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY BRIGHTLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the son of last witness—I live with my father—on Monday the 8th of April, about seven o'clock, I was with Taylor at the top of the lane, about thirty yards from home, and saw the two prisoners go into the house—they went quietly in at the door—I did not see how they got in—I directly went and knocked at the door which was shut—I heard one say to the other, "Don't open the door"—I called Taylor, and told him to get over the fence, and get in the back way which he did—I heard them come down stairs—I got over the fence myself and saw both of them in the back yard—I heard them run up stairs again, and Hatter opened the door, he made use of a very bad expression, and said he would knock my eye out—he knocked me down—I got up again—he ran down Crossfield-lane, and down a turning where there is no thoroughfare—I there caught him, and gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1666" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1666" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1666" type="surname" value="RANDALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1666" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE RANDALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Crossfield-lane, Deptford. I saw the pri<lb></lb>soners come out of the prosecutor's house and run away—I did not know them before—I went after Thompson and took him—I did not say any thing—he offered me 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. if I would let him go.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you lose sight of him at all? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—when I took him, he said, "I am <hi rend="italic">done.</hi>"</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1667" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1667" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1667" type="surname" value="BRIGHTLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1667" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL BRIGHTLEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I came home between seven and eight o'clock—I found a bag under the range—I took it out, and found in it four skeleton keys and a small wrench bar about a foot long—I gave them to the officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Who lives in the house besides you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No one—I rent it.</p>
